ha versions in production risks these breaking changes. Either pin to stable 6.6.0 or thoroughly test schema generation, validation, authentication middleware, and client codegen before proceeding with 7.0.0-alpha.0.\n\n\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>\U0001f916 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>\n\n\n\n```\n\nIn `@src/controller/home_today_schedule_controller.ts` around lines 5 - 10, The\n\nproject is using an unstable tsoa 7.0.0-alpha.0 which may break OpenAPI/schema\n\ngeneration and auth/validation; update package.json to pin tsoa to the latest\n\nstable 6.6.0 (or revert any explicit 7.x alpha entries), run npm/yarn install,\n\nregenerate types/ OpenAPI artifacts, and run tests that exercise\n\nTodayWorkController (and other controllers using `@Route`(\'works\') / Controller\n\nbase class) to validate schema names, nullable/optional handling, host/servers\n\nURLs, and authentication behavior before deploying; alternatively, postpone\n\nproduction deployment until thorough compatibility testing with 7.0.0-alpha.0 is\n\ncompleted.\n\n```\n\n\n\n</details>\n\n\n\n<!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:ocelot -->\n\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit -->\n\n\n\n> +  @Get(\'{userId}/today/summary\')\n\n+  public async getTodaySummary(\n\n+    @Path() userId: string,\n\n+  ): Promise<TodayWorkSummaryResponse> {\n\n+    return GET_TODAY_WORK_SUMMARY(userId);\n\n+  }\n\n\n\n_\u26a0\ufe0f Potential issue_ | _\U0001f7e0 Major_\n\n\n\n**Add error handling and consider input validation.**\n\n\n\nThe endpoint lacks error handling. If `GET_TODAY_WORK_SUMMARY` throws (e.g., database error, user not found), the exception will propagate unhandled, potentially exposing stack traces or causing 500 responses without meaningful error messages.\n\n\n\nAdditionally, since `userId` is expected to be a UUID (per JSDoc), consider validating the format before calling the service.\n\n\n\n\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>\U0001f6e0\ufe0f Suggested improvement with error handling</summary