isits to Google\n\nPlay. You can browse by date and by topic, and delete part or all of your\n\nactivity.\n\n\n\nGo to My Activity\n\n<https://myactivity.google.com/myactivity?utm_source=pp&hl=en>.\n\n\n\n*Google Dashboard*\n\n\n\nGoogle Dashboard allows you to manage information associated with specific\n\nproducts.\n\n\n\nGo to Dashboard <https://myaccount.google.com/dashboard?utm_source=pp&hl=en>\n\n.\n\n\n\n*Your Personal Information*\n\n\n\nManage your contact information, such as your name, email, and phone number.\n\n\n\nGo to Personal Info\n\n<https://myaccount.google.com/privacy?utm_source=pp&hl=en#personalinfo>.\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\n*If you use the Google Payments service provided by Google Payment Korea\n\nLLC, the Google Payments Privacy Notice below also provides details on how\n\nyour personal information is processed in that service.*\n\n\n\nGoogle Payments Privacy Notice:\n\nhttps://payments.google.com/payments/apis-secure/get_legal_document?ldo=0&ldt=privacynotice&ldl=ko\n\n\n\nYour purchases, credit history, and/or transaction information is available\n\nto you via a number of secure online tools we provide to all users to\n\naccess data. Sign in to your Google Account <https://myaccount.google.com/>\n\nto get an overview of the ways you use Google\'s services and access that\n\ndata.\n\n\n\nYou can also export your transaction history with Google Takeout:\n\n\n\n    1. Go to takeout.google.com.\n\n    2. Once the Google Takeout page opens, click *Deselect all*.\n\n    3. Select *Google Pay*.\n\n    4. At the bottom, click *Next step*.\n\n    5. In the 2nd section, select the file type, frequency, and destination.\n\n    6. Click *Create export*.\n\n\n\nFor more information, please visit the How to download your Google data\n\n<https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/3024190> Help Center article.\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\n*If you use Google Cloud service provided by Google, the Google Cloud\n\nPrivacy Notice be